social_posts.post_text: “Happy New Ear!” as my two year old screams it! Happy New Year everyone. We spent the day at the incredible Australia Zoo with four of my littles (5 of 6 behind me, lol), soaking up school holidays, sunlight and the good vibes of what looks to be a beautiful year. My best wishes to you and yours, Em xx 📸: my boy Ryder Jack, 7 years old!!
Late to the Valentine’s Day party but always on time with this one. You are my return, my respite and my resuscitation back to life. Thank you for our extraordinary love ❤️ @hello_azureantoinette

Just dropped!!! This year, in celebration of International Women’s Day, @decjuba and @businesschicks are raising funds for @thehungerprojectau with our Strong, Smart, Brave tees. Get yours online at Decjuba today (link in my bio). Pictured here with the strong, smart, brave Founder of Decjuba, @taniadecjuba

We all need reminders of why we do what we do. Sydney delivered that yesterday morning, in the shape of a beautiful IWD celebration with 1000 friends - some old and loyal, some new and hopeful - but we were all there for the same reason. To support women and celebrate what happens when we do this together. I’ve seen firsthand how destructive it is when we don’t do this and I’ve seen the power of what can come of life when we do. Let’s choose the latter. Big thanks to all the beautiful people that pulled this one off: @yemipenn, @thequeenofconfidence @hello_azureantoinette @shellyhorton1 @kaela.mcrae @taniadecjuba @decjuba @franniemae_music @rmarfatia19 @cgray0902 @bondi_road_balloons @carolineo_hutchison @perfecteventsoz @smiledarlingphotos @taylorrose__p and my mum and sister who were there placing out programs with the crew at 5am! See you next week Brisbane and Melbourne! #iwd2023 #businesschicks #crackthecode #getitdone

That’s a wrap on our Los Angeles Knowledge + Study Tour. It was a joy to be back home in LA and a joy to experience this week alongside incredible women who came along for the ride, all of whom I’d do anything for and all of whom will be lifelong friends. We’re already in planning for our next Study Tour because these are so fab and we all need more joy to look forward to. Tell me - would you prefer we focused on a New York one or a Silicon Valley one toward the end of this year?? Taking votes now and so grateful for the belly laughs, the learning, the deep listening and connection and all the wine + food from this week too. Epic! #businesschicks #ucla #disneyland #knowledgeandstudytour2023

Cheers to my love, this rockstar @hello_azureantoinette who says yes to my crazy ideas and only ever asks questions afterwards. These past few weeks we’ve seen more airport terminals and hotel rooms than most see in years and today was our last @businesschicks event for IWD. She smashed it, as did the team, and @yemi.penn and @bodyimagemovement too. This has been a season Az, and I’m happy and so grateful you’re in it xx

A few weeks ago I was asked to speak for @businesswomenaw so I flew into Albury amidst all the IWD action and had a blast with them. Before my speech, the organisers gave away $5,000 grants to three local businesswomen (@therealfloristalbury, @bluechaiofficial and @bobbydazzlerdresses_) which had the entire room lit! Inspired by @dream_accounting and @starfishmarketing1 who’d funded these grants, on the spot I decided to give away three $2,500 grants to the runner up finalists (@bordermidwiferycare @simonetylee and @solpadel). I hope you’ll join me in congratulating all these amazing women who together show us what it means to support one another where you can and how you can and we look forward to watching as your businesses continue to soar!! #womenactuallysupportingwomen #businesschicks #IWD2023

Here are some memories, some pieces of joy, and lots of fun masking as work. Such a privilege to host my magnificent love @hello_azureantoinette and her Show + Tell event last night at the @businesschicks HQ and catch up with beautiful friends who feel like family. Little Louis even made a brief cameo! Thanks to our incredible team for all their love and hard work and to @smiledarlingphotos for capturing the moments we never want to miss.
Thrilled to be here at @pwc_au’s The Outside with these two rockstars @hello_azureantoinette and @drginacleo - what a privilege and honour! #ExperienceTheOutside #PwC #TheOutside

Our beautiful Poppy passed on Saturday. He was such a huge influence on me and his support knew no end. Poppy would come into the office for a cup of tea every Tuesday for years to sit with me and talk with all the girls. Each week, he’d bring me newspaper cut outs of businesswomen that he thought I should know about. He didn’t miss a Business Chicks event for years and only ever had positive things to say about others. In his 91 years I never heard him speak ill of anyone. He was the hardest worker I’ve known and had a huge heart: he donated blood over 600 times, volunteered with ‘the oldies’ at Meals on Wheels for 15 years, and gave his time and skills at the Australian Heritage Fleet where he’d spend two days each week volunteering. He was proud to receive an Order of Australia medal for his contributions and we were all proud to know him. He was kind, giving and had a work ethic I hope to think I inherited. We’re all going to miss you Poppy and are so grateful for all you gave us.

I am overjoyed, honoured and thrilled to be presenting Dame Jacinda Ardern for three special events in Sydney, Melbourne and Canberra in August. Huge gratitude to my @businesschicks team and our incredible and compassionate community. Thank you, thank you, thank you. Tickets are live on the Business Chicks site now and I can’t wait to see you all there!

This month five years ago I released Winging It into the world. I worked my backside off on that book, hoping to cram as much knowledge as I had into the pages, making sure no words were wasted and every sentence counted. It’s been reprinted 12 times in Australia, was published in the US, Canada and Poland and continues to sell nicely. If you bought it, I’m grateful. If you read it, that’s even better 😂. I was supported by some amazing people - @lucyormonde and @ingridohlsson in particular - and will always be grateful for the highs, lows, learnings and lack of sleep that book writing brings. I’ve met countless people that have told me they started businesses, closed businesses, left jobs, changed careers, took big leaps, backed themselves, found lost enthusiasm and did something they thought themselves not capable of. If that’s the truth then it’s mission accomplished for me. I’d love to tell you I’m working on a third book but the truth is my hands are full and I’m finding it hard to locate the discipline required to put something exceptional out into the world. It’s brewing though! Much love (and keep winging it!) xo

Here’s the face of a happy 41 year old. Thank you for being born @hello_azureantoinette - you give so much to me, to us, to the world. I’ll never stop being in awe of your talents, sense of humour, goofiness, knowledge, compassion, patience and capacity for love. Enjoy being spoilt today Bub xxx

Butterflies in my tummy this morning as we kick off our Australian tour with Professor Jimmy Choo. Gold Coast is happening this Friday and then four other cities (Brisbane, Melbourne, Sydney and Perth) next week and the one after. It’s not too late to join us so head to the @businesschicks site for tickets. We could also do with a few behind-the-scenes helping hands so if you’re interested in joining the crew who makes the magic happen in any of those cities drop us a note at events@businesschicks.com. Sending love to everyone for an awesome week ahead! E x

There are less dramatic ways to take some time off and nicer places I’d choose to spend it than a hospital bed but that’s what I got last week. Instead of finishing up our tour with Professor Jimmy Choo, I spent four days on an IV drip with a nasty bacterial infection (no one can quite say how I got it 🤷‍♀️ ). This is the second time in my life when my head wouldn’t allow me to collapse from stress so my body made the decision for me. Here are some exciting highlights for you from the events I managed to get to, and also please note how @hello_azureantoinette likes to take the medical thunder wherever she goes, falling out and going unconscious in the ER while I’m half-dying and looking on. I knew we were in the best place for it so I just rolled my eyes, picked up my phone and snapped her laying on the ground while the nurses ran around after her instead of me worrying about her for once 😂😂😂😂. What a time. But srsly, my hot fiancée, @hello_azureantoinette, thank you for being by my side and advocating for me when I couldn’t. When the paramedics took my temp at 38.9 I said ‘I’ll be fine - just need to sleep it off’ and Azure said ‘hell no, get in that ambulance’ and didn’t stop protecting me until I was out and safely in her arms again. Thank you to my extraordinary @businesschicks team who stepped up in my absence and @shellyhorton1 @spoonful_of_sarah @hello_azureantoinette and @jess_wilson_nutrition who held the stage while I lay wondering when I could break free. I’m out of hospital now and can’t say I’m quite ready to take on the world but gimme a few more days and I’ll consider it. E x

Alright. Tickets for the last @businesschicks event of the year go on sale in just over an hour so be ready and waiting by your computer/phone at 10am AEDT and we’ll see you in Melbourne for a morning with Sir Richard Branson on Dec 11. Who’s coming??? PS There’s a member reunion dinner happening the night before and this is live on the site now so make sure you register for that one too!

In case anyone apart from my mum is interested in this, I have a new website. Boom! Go check it out at emmaisaacs.com and HUGE thanks to the dynamic duo @hello_azureantoinette and @jordanne.co who designed it together. Dream team. They didn’t even ask me one question and just got it done and nailed it. Thank you @hello_azureantoinette for the brand design and thank you for always making me laugh in awkward photo shoots that I loathe 😂😂
I hosted a party with my Ken last night at the @businesschicks HQ. Ken dj’d and we ran amok and I didn’t stack it in my rollerskates which was possibly the biggest miracle of the  night 😂

This will never relieve the pain and damage caused but it’s a small step in the right direction. Moral to the story: do not believe everything you read in the media and stand up for yourself if you can find the strength and courage xxxx

Grateful for this day which my spirit needed after a heinous year of mistruths, injustice and downright canceling. People will do what they can to bring you down as it makes them feel better and more powerful in the moment, but if you can somehow muster the strength and tenacity to believe in yourself again, you can’t hide who you really are nor argue with the integrity you have in your heart. It was a joy to talk with my dear friend @richardbranson this morning at our last @businesschicks event of the year today and an elation to be swept up in the wonder of women who also have integrity and believe in supporting one another, even if at times it feels lonely and as if the world you’ve built around you has deserted you. We had a beautiful member dinner last night that carried on well into the morning meaning we collected approximately three hours sleep before this morning’s event. I’d do it again and again and again if it meant something to someone. (Also PS, how cute is my mum in the last pic who continues to be astounded at the ridiculous, untrue allegations but shows up regardless) - love you mama! And thanks for the pics @smiledarlingphotos and to @hello_azureantoinette and @spoonful_of_sarah who led this morning with their usual chutzpah and charm. And to my team of rockstars who continue to bring to life this work - this one’s for you. It always will be. Em xx

Happy New Year friends. May you all experience as much love and as many giggles as this little guy gives us! Louis’ current obsessions are pink hats and a random collection of cars that come everywhere with us. Thank you for the photos, my ❤️ and stepmom extraordinaire @hello_azureantoinette
